args: Rgh, the traitor prince?! I'd hoped to get\nthis over with before he noticed. Hurry!\nBind the trueblood!
The Empire is after her?!\nVania! Are you hurt?!
Oh, I'm fine. They just startled me a little.\nI'm not afraid of these mooks!
Huh? No, I can fight! You know I'm tough.\nThis'll go way quicker if we team up.
There, see? No problem! And if it's me\nAND my bloodkin's power together, we—
VANIA! That's why I told you to hide behind\nme!
What? Why?! If you'd just work with me\nhere, we'd be through with these chumps\nin two seconds!
It's just the two of them! Surround them\nand strike from all sides! Use our numbers!
Even more reinforcements?\nThis isn't good. At this rate—
We have the advantage!\nNow! Seize the vampire!
Are you all right, {player_name}?\nThe Knights of Levin will take this fight.\nI'll open a path for your retreat!
We can speak once we're to safety.\nFor now, RUN!
You too, Yurius? All right... Understood.\nVania, can you stand? We need to get\naway from this place!
We should be past their reach here.\nNow... Albert, Yurius. Why are you here?
You both left the Halidom in search of the\nseeds of the abyss.
Indeed. Our probe revealed that Phares\nhad given seeds to a number of soldiers\nas part of some experiment.
We chased those rumors here, determined\nto put a stop to whatever he's planning.
What?! You believe my brother is trying to\nuse Vania and the seeds to some ill end?
We don't know the specifics any better\nthan you, but he is all but certainly\nplotting something, and they're involved.
Hey, what are these ＂seeds of the abyss＂?
An extremely dangerous breed of dragon.\nThey are too great a force for mankind to\nwield. Should they try...this is the result.
Ew, what IS that?! It's all wriggly and\nslimy and...EWWW!
That is the price of said hubris. The seeds\nfeed on human mana and fuse with it.\nThey are a cursed thing.
Now, a group of extremists within the\nEmpire who hold the seeds seek vampire\nblood. The situation grows ever more grim.
And Vania will continue to be a target until\nwe stop them.
Exactly. Which brings me to a proposal.\nWill you allow us to serve as her guards?
Doing so would help us in our quest to\ndestroy the seeds as well. A mutually\nbeneficial arrangement for all parties.
I agree. The information you've uncovered\nwhile tracking them will be vital to figuring\nout how the extremists knew about her.
But we've yet to hear the most important\nopinion on the matter. What say you,\nVania?
Fine by me. A friend of yours is a friend\nof mine.
Nice to have you on board,\nUncle Sparky. Uncle Slimy.
You? The lightning magic guy is Sparky,\nand you, Mr. Unspeakable Tentacles man,\nyou're Uncle Slimy.
Adjectives aside, I'm still not of an age fit\nto be anyone's... *ahem* It matters not.\nWe need to formulate our plan.
{player_name}, let us pool our\nintel about the seeds and the trueblood to\nsee if we can turn up a link between them.
We still know little of vampires,\nlet alone their higher echelon.
Of course. I'm no expert myself,\nbut here's what I've gathered so far...
...He's just droning on and on. Everything\ncoming out of his mouth is so complicated.\nI'm bored.
Right. I'm going out to the garden.
What has you sneaking off to sigh in\nsecret, my little troublemaker?
WAUGH! Don't scare me like that, Uncle\nSlimy! And can't you tell? I'm depressed.
My bloodkin's completely ignoring me.\nToday's been awful from start to finish.
It finally felt like we were getting to know\neach other a little and starting to gel, but\nthen he wouldn't work with me at all.
I guess our bond's still too weak. How am\nI supposed to take it to the next level?
Ah, I see now. I fear you've been laboring\nunder a misconception from the very start.
Bonds are neither forged nor tempered\nintentionally.
Bonds grow stronger on their own as you\nlearn about, care for, and trust another. At\nleast, that has always been my experience.
I certainly can't recall ever attempting to\nintentionally strengthen my connection to\nthe captain.
Indeed, I even sought to sever that tie,\nonce. But he trusted in me so thoroughly\nthat all my designs failed... The jerk.
Hmmm... So you're saying there's not\nenough trust between us.
At the very least, the softhearted prince\ndoes not yet seem to regard you as an\nequal.
Rather, he seems to view you as a child—\na little sister to be shielded from harm.\nDo you not get the same impression?
Ah...! He DID say something like that! Ugh,\nhow many times do I have to tell him that\nI'M the older sibling here?!
I suspected as much. Then your first step\nmust be to win his respect as a peer.
Make him acknowledge your strength as\nyou fight these foes. Prove you are no\nhelpless waif.
Yeah... Yeah! Okay, got it! I just need to\nprove that I'm the mistress around here!
That's exactly what I thought at first, too.\nI'll give it another try!
You're a surprisingly nice guy,\nUncle Slimy. I appreciate this!
Hah. I've done nothing worthy of thanks.\nI just saw you looking so pathetic that I\ncouldn't keep my mouth shut. That's all.
